<<fig-gratio, fig.cap="g-ratio proxy derived from QMT bound pool fraction (preliminary). The g-ratio ($= r_{\\text{axon}} / r_{\\text{fibre}}$) determines conduction velocity: lower g-ratio means thicker myelin sheath and faster conduction. Combined with AxCaliber axon diameter from ses-02 DWI, this yields per-tract conduction velocity matrices (\\textbf{D}) that replace the uniform 7\\,m/s assumption in whole-brain simulations.", fig.height=3>>=
